For packages that have been symlinked into more than one package (say, via `npm install --link`) I am seeing the referenced code more than once.

In `node` you only get the package once so I guess they're using physical path whereas maybe browserify is using the logical path.

I have provided more information below to clarify.

``` bash
$ # TESTED VERSION
$ browserify --version
2.22.0
```

``` bash
$ # TEST PACKAGES (STRUCTURE)
$ tree */
a/
├── index.js
└── package.json
b/
├── index.js
├── node_modules/
│   └── a -> ../../a/
└── package.json
c/
├── index.js
├── node_modules/
│   ├── a -> ../../a/
│   └── b -> ../../b/
└── package.json

5 directories, 6 files
```

``` bash
$ # TEST PACKAGES (CONTENTS)
$ head */index.js
==> a/index.js <==
console.log("A");

==> b/index.js <==
var a = require("a");
console.log("B");

==> c/index.js <==
var a = require("a"),
    b = require("b");
console.log("C");
```

``` bash
$ # TEST PACKAGES BEHAVIOR (node)
$ node a
A
$ node b
A
B
$ node c
A
B
C
```

``` bash
